# Batch Maker — Master To-Do List
_Last updated: 2026-02-25_

---

## 🐛 Bugs — Fix Before Launch

- [x] **Page wipe on action** — Any action (cancel batch, mark ordered, etc.) cleared the entire page until manual refresh. **FIXED** in `dashboard.tsx` via `useRef` for `selectedLocationId` — fetch functions now always read the current location value, not a stale closure.
- [x] **Archive feature missing from website** — Workflow archive/unarchive with restore now in `DashboardWorkflows.tsx`. Active workflows show an Archive button; archived workflows are hidden behind a collapsible "Show archived (n)" toggle with a Restore button. Matches mobile app behaviour.
- [x] **Team status display broken** — Fixed in `dashboard.tsx` via `fetchClockedInMembers()` which queries `time_entries WHERE clock_out IS NULL AND owner_id = user.id`, then filters by `location_id` when a specific location is selected. Polls every 30 seconds and passes result down as `clockedInMembers` prop.

---

## 🟠 Pre-Launch — Core Features

### Account & Access
- [x] **Account tiers** — Maintain two separate account pages (standard and premium). Standard users must not see premium/production tools — both to avoid overwhelm and to maintain value in the premium tier.
- [ ] **New user tutorial** — Interactive onboarding walkthrough for first-time users (tooltips, guided steps, sample workflow).

### Employee & Location
- [x] **Employee directory** — Active / On Leave / Terminated status on `network_member_roles` (not profiles). No photos. Employees can work at multiple businesses.
- [x] **Employment status gate** — `canClockIn()` blocks terminated and on_leave employees at the API level.
- [ ] **Location locking** — Employees can only clock in within ~100m of the registered business address.
  - Food trucks: when start-of-day report is submitted, record a GPS ping; all staff must clock in within ~100m of that ping.
  - Multiple trucks require separate licenses; no simultaneous sign-in across physically separate locations.
  - Ghost kitchens running multiple brands from one address are fine on a single license (data will not be separated by brand).
  - Implementation: capture `navigator.geolocation` on clock-in, compare against `locations.lat/lng` in `canClockIn()`.

### Workflows & Batches
- [ ] **Workflow caching & public directory** — Cache AI-parsed workflow results to avoid duplicate parse costs. Build a browsable "Workflow Directory" for importing community workflows.
  - Only scrape recipe ingredients and steps — no blog content (copyright risk).
  - Enforce no blog post attachments.
  - Parse workflows for equipment references (required vs. recommended).
- [ ] **Barcode / QR printing (app)** — Print a QR code tied to an active batch (useful mid-fermentation etc.). Scanning the QR with the app:
  - Imports the batch and opens it at the last completed step.
  - Allows the scanning user to claim it.
  - Printing the QR should release the workflow from any user who currently holds it.

